---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
title="Google Ads Headline Generator (Free RSA Headline Ideas)"
description="Generate Google Ads headline ideas instantly. Improve ad copy, test variations, and boost CTR with this free headline generator."
currentPath="/google-ads-headline-generator"
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <h1>Google Ads Headline Generator</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Generate Google Ads headline ideas for responsive search ads and check whether they fit within the 30-character limit.
    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="card tool-card">
    <div class="field">
      <label for="keyword">Main Keyword</label>
      <input id="keyword" type="text" placeholder="e.g. Microsoft 365 subscription" />
    </div>

    <div class="field">
      <label for="offer">Offer or Benefit</label>
      <input id="offer" type="text" placeholder="e.g. Save 30% today" />
    </div>

    <div class="field">
      <label for="brand">Brand or Site Name (optional)</label>
      <input id="brand" type="text" placeholder="e.g. PPC Toolbench" />
    </div>

    <div class="button-row">
      <button class="btn-primary" id="generateBtn" type="button">Generate Headlines</button>
      <button class="btn-secondary" id="resetBtn" type="button">Reset</button>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card results-card">
    <h2>Generated Headlines</h2>
    <div id="results" class="results-list">
      <p class="empty-state">Your generated headline ideas will appear here.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card content-card">
    <h2>What This Tool Does</h2>
    <p>
      This Google Ads headline generator helps you quickly create headline ideas for responsive
      search ads. It combines your keyword, offer, and brand terms into multiple headline variations
      that can be used as ad copy inspiration.
    </p>

    <h2>Why It Matters</h2>
    <p>
      Google Ads headlines have limited space, and strong headline variations can improve click-through
      rate and overall ad relevance. This tool helps you brainstorm faster while keeping the standard
      30-character limit in mind.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Use It</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Enter your main keyword.</li>
      <li>Add your offer, benefit, or value proposition.</li>
      <li>Optionally add your brand or site name.</li>
      <li>Click Generate Headlines to see multiple variations.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Related Tools</h2>
<p>
  Pair this with our
  <a href="/google-ads-description-generator">Google Ads Description Generator</a>,
  validate copy using the
  <a href="/google-ads-character-counter">Google Ads Character Counter</a>,
  preview layouts with the
  <a href="/google-ads-preview-tool">Google Ads Preview Tool</a>,
  or build tracking links with the
  <a href="/utm-builder">UTM Builder</a>.
</p>
  </section>

<section class="card content-card">
  <h2>How to Write Better Google Ads Headlines</h2>
  <p>
    Strong Google Ads headlines play a major role in ad performance. They help
    capture attention, communicate value quickly, and improve click-through
    rate by making your message more relevant to the searcher.
  </p>

  <p>
    A useful headline should be clear, specific, and aligned with the user's
    intent. Instead of using vague wording, focus on benefits, offers, and
    direct value propositions that match the campaign goal.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Highlight a clear benefit or offer</li>
    <li>Use simple and direct language</li>
    <li>Match the searcher's intent</li>
    <li>Avoid repeating the same wording across headlines</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to Use This Google Ads Headline Generator</h2>
  <p>
    This tool helps you generate headline ideas for responsive search ads.
    You can use it to brainstorm new angles, test different messaging ideas,
    and improve the variety of your ad combinations before launch.
  </p>

  <ol>
    <li>Enter your product, service, or campaign topic</li>
    <li>Review the generated headline ideas</li>
    <li>Pick the strongest options based on clarity and intent</li>
    <li>Test combinations that support different search contexts</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Why Headline Variety Matters in Responsive Search Ads</h2>
  <p>
    Google Ads responsive search ads rely on multiple headline combinations.
    If your headlines all say nearly the same thing, you reduce the system's
    flexibility and miss opportunities to match different user intents.
  </p>

  <p>
    A stronger set of headlines usually includes a mix of value-focused,
    trust-focused, and action-focused messaging. This helps create ads that are
    more useful, more readable, and more competitive.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Use one headline for the main offer</li>
    <li>Use one headline for trust or credibility</li>
    <li>Use one headline for urgency or action</li>
    <li>Keep each line distinct and purposeful</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>What is a Google Ads headline generator?</h3>
  <p>
    A Google Ads headline generator is a tool that helps advertisers create
    headline ideas for search campaigns faster and more efficiently.
  </p>

  <h3>Why are headlines important in Google Ads?</h3>
  <p>
    Headlines are often the first part of the ad people notice. Better
    headlines can improve clarity, relevance, and click-through rate.
  </p>

  <h3>How many headlines should I create for responsive search ads?</h3>
  <p>
    It is helpful to create multiple headline variations so Google can test
    different combinations and match ads more effectively to user searches.
  </p>

  <h2>Related Tools</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/google-ads-preview-tool">Google Ads Preview Tool</a></li>
    <li><a href="/google-ads-character-counter">Google Ads Character Counter</a></li>
    <li><a href="/google-ads-description-generator">Google Ads Description Generator</a></li>
    <li><a href="/utm-builder">UTM Builder</a></li>
  </ul>
</section>

  <script>
    const keywordEl = document.getElementById("keyword");
    const offerEl = document.getElementById("offer");
    const brandEl = document.getElementById("brand");
    const generateBtn = document.getElementById("generateBtn");
    const resetBtn = document.getElementById("resetBtn");
    const resultsEl = document.getElementById("results");

    function trimText(text) {
      return text.trim();
    }

    function cutToLimit(text, limit = 30) {
      return text.length > limit ? text.slice(0, limit) : text;
    }

    function generateHeadlines() {
      const keyword = trimText(keywordEl.value);
      const offer = trimText(offerEl.value);
      const brand = trimText(brandEl.value);

      if (!keyword || !offer) {
        resultsEl.innerHTML = '<p class="empty-state">Please enter both a main keyword and an offer or benefit.</p>';
        return;
      }

      const rawHeadlines = [
        `${keyword} - ${offer}`,
        `${offer} ${keyword}`,
        `Buy ${keyword} Today`,
        `${keyword} Deals Now`,
        `${keyword} Special Offer`,
        `${offer} - Shop Now`,
        `${keyword} Online`,
        `${keyword} For Less`,
        `${offer} Today`,
        brand ? `${keyword} | ${brand}` : "",
        brand ? `${offer} | ${brand}` : "",
        brand ? `${brand} ${keyword}` : ""
      ].filter(Boolean);

      const uniqueHeadlines = [...new Set(rawHeadlines)].map((item) => cutToLimit(item, 30));

      resultsEl.innerHTML = uniqueHeadlines.map((headline) => {
        const count = headline.length;
        const statusClass = count <= 30 ? "ok" : "danger";
        const statusText = count <= 30 ? "Fits" : "Too Long";

        return `
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="result-top">
              <strong>${headline}</strong>
              <span class="status ${statusClass}">${statusText}</span>
            </div>
            <div class="result-meta">${count} / 30 characters</div>
          </div>
        `;
      }).join("");
    }

    function resetForm() {
      keywordEl.value = "";
      offerEl.value = "";
      brandEl.value = "";
      resultsEl.innerHTML = '<p class="empty-state">Your generated headline ideas will appear here.</p>';
    }

    generateBtn.addEventListener("click", generateHeadlines);
    resetBtn.addEventListener("click", resetForm);
  </script>

  <style>
    .page-header {
      margin-bottom: 24px;
    }

    .tool-card,
    .results-card,
    .content-card {
      margin-top: 24px;
    }

    .field {
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    label {
      display: block;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }

    input {
      width: 100%;
      padding: 14px 16px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      font-size: 1rem;
      background: #fff;
    }

    input:focus {
      outline: 2px solid rgba(109, 40, 217, 0.15);
      border-color: var(--primary);
    }

    .button-row {
      display: flex;
      gap: 12px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }

    button {
      border: 0;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 12px 16px;
      font-size: 0.98rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      cursor: pointer;
    }

    .btn-primary {
      background: var(--primary);
      color: white;
    }

    .btn-primary:hover {
      background: var(--primary-hover);
    }

    .btn-secondary {
      background: #ede9fe;
      color: #4c1d95;
    }

    .results-list {
      display: grid;
      gap: 12px;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .result-item {
      border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 14px 16px;
      background: #fff;
    }

    .result-top {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      gap: 12px;
      align-items: center;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    .result-meta {
      margin-top: 8px;
      color: #6b7280;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .empty-state {
      color: #6b7280;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .status {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 4px 10px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 700;
    }

    .status.ok {
      background: #ecfdf5;
      color: #065f46;
    }

    .status.danger {
      background: #fef2f2;
      color: #991b1b;
    }

    .content-card h2 {
      margin-top: 28px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .content-card h2:first-child {
      margin-top: 0;
    }

    .content-card p,
    .content-card li {
      color: #374151;
      font-size: 1.02rem;
      line-height: 1.75;
    }
  </style>
</MainLayout>